Bulls, Heat Take 3-0 Leads in NBA Playoff Series; Portland Beats Dallas

-- B y   R o b   G l o s t e r
-- 
2011-04-22T05:33:45Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-22/bulls-heat-take-3-0-leads-in-nba-playoff-series-portland-beats-dallas.html
The  Miami Heat  and Chicago Bulls
won playoff games on the road last night to take 3-0 leads in
their first-round National Basketball Association series. The
Portland Trail Blazers won at home against the  Dallas Mavericks 
to pull within 2-1 in their series.  Dwyane Wade had 32 points, 10 rebounds and 8 assists, and
LeBron James added 24 points and 15 rebounds, in the Heat’s 100-
94 victory in Philadelphia against the 76ers.  Derrick Rose ’s layup with 17 seconds remaining broke a tie
in the Bulls’ 88-84 win at the Indiana Pacers. Rose had 23
points and Luol Deng had 21 to lead Chicago.  Portland got 25 points from Wesley Matthews and 20 from
LaMarcus Aldridge in its 97-92 victory. Jason Terry had 29
points and Dirk Nowitzki had 25 for  Dallas .  The New York Knicks, trailing the Boston Celtics 2-0 in
their series, are home tonight in Game 3. Amar’e Stoudemire
(back spasms) and Chauncey Billups (strained left knee) missed
practice for the Knicks yesterday.  Orlando is at Atlanta tonight for Game 3 of their series,
which is tied 1-1. The Los Angeles Lakers and New Orleans
Hornets are tied 1-1 in their series, with the third game
tonight in New Orleans.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Rob Gloster in San Francisco at 
